#: src/views/Agents.tsx
msgid "<0>Action needed to activate.</0> Codex leaves a new hook dormant until you trust it: open the Codex CLI, run <1>/hooks</1>, and trust the Belay hook. Until then this agent is <2>not actively protected</2>. Even once trusted, Codex hooks fire on <3>shell commands, edits, and MCP calls - not plain file reads</3>, and apply only to <4>local tasks, not Codex Cloud</4>runs. Treat this as a strong guardrail, not a guarantee."
msgstr "<0>Action needed to activate.</0> Codex leaves a new hook dormant until you trust it: open the Codex CLI, run <1>/hooks</1>, and trust the Belay hook. Until then this agent is <2>not actively protected</2>. Even once trusted, Codex hooks fire on <3>shell commands, edits, and MCP calls - not plain file reads</3>, and apply only to <4>local tasks, not Codex Cloud</4>runs. Treat this as a strong guardrail, not a guarantee."

#: src/views/Agents.tsx
msgid "<0>What Belay can and can't enforce.</0> Belay blocks agents that run through a cooperative hook — the <1>Claude Code CLI</1>, <2>Cursor</2>, and the <3>Codex CLI</3> (once trusted). The <4>Claude Desktop</4> and<5>ChatGPT desktop</5> apps are detected here, but they run their tools in a separate sandbox that bypasses these hooks, so Belay can't block them yet. Deeper coverage for desktop apps needs OS-level interception (an optional, admin-enabled tier)."
msgstr "<0>What Belay can and can't enforce.</0> Belay blocks agents that run through a cooperative hook — the <1>Claude Code CLI</1>, <2>Cursor</2>, and the <3>Codex CLI</3> (once trusted). The <4>Claude Desktop</4> and<5>ChatGPT desktop</5> apps are detected here, but they run their tools in a separate sandbox that bypasses these hooks, so Belay can't block them yet. Deeper coverage for desktop apps needs OS-level interception (an optional, admin-enabled tier)."

